				<h4 class="env">Environment</h4>
				<a href="javascript:void()" class='Development'>Development</a>
				<a href="javascript:void()" >Production</a>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div id="mainContent">
			<p>Specify the site ID you want to review. If you are not sure what the ID is, try the <a href="javascript:void()">Customer Type Search Form</a>.</p>
			<p>Fon/Site ID: <input type="text" name="siteNumber" id="siteNumber" value="" size="6" maxsize="6" />
			<input type="button" name="Go" id="go" value="Go" onclick="window.location.href='display.htm'" /></p>
			<p>Note that any data in the development environment is merely a copy of old production data. It does not reflect actual development data. Any changes made here will not be reflected in the production environment.</p>
			<p id="noID" class="warning"></p>
		</div>
		<input type="hidden" name="pageAction" value="start" />
	</form>
